Class Graph

java.lang.Object
  Graph

public class Graph
extends java.lang.Object

The Graph class represents a collection of Edges and Vertices which form a Graph.

Author:
Kevin Scroggins

addEdge

public void addEdge(Edge e)
Adds the specified Edge to the collection of Edges if it is not already contained in the Graph. Also adds both Vertices to the Graph if they are not already contained in the collection of Vertices. If either of the Edge's Vertices are already in the Graph, the Edge is set to reference the Vertex so there are no duplicate Vertices.

Parameters:
e - the Edge to be added to the Graph.

writeTo

public void writeTo(java.io.PrintWriter out)
             throws java.io.IOException
Writes the Graph to the specified PrintWriter. Outputs the Graph to the format: " x1, y1; x2, y2" where x1 and y1 are the x and y coordinates of the first Vertex of the Edge and x2 and y2 are the x and y coordinates of the second Vertex of the Edge for each Edge contained within the Graph.

Parameters:
out - the PrintWriter to write the Graph to.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if there was an error writing to the output stream.
